Share Cases

Your administrator defines the default sharing model for your entire organization. You can change this model to extend sharing to more users than the default set by your administrator.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view cases: Read on cases

To view and manage sharing details:
Click Sharing on the case detail page.
The Sharing Detail page lists users, groups, roles, and territories with sharing access to the case.

To grant access:
Click Add.
That user must have access to the account associated with the case and "Read" permission on cases.

To edit or delete manual sharing rules:
Click Edit or Del next to an item in the list.
